# Core workflow

- Read and follow the project-root `AGENTS.md` before substantial work.
- If the request is analysis, planning, review, research, diagnosis, or explanation only, do not edit files.
- Before implementation, identify observable acceptance criteria and inspect relevant code, tests, configuration, and current changes.
- Keep the change minimal and within scope. Do not perform unrelated refactors, upgrades, formatting sweeps, or API changes.
- Do not fabricate commands, files, APIs, outputs, tests, logs, benchmarks, or external responses.
- Never expose secrets or perform destructive, production, irreversible, or real-money actions without explicit authorization.
- If Plan mode is active, produce and refine the plan only. Do not edit files or run mutating commands until the user explicitly starts implementation.
- At completion, provide actual verification evidence and mark unavailable checks as unverified.
